t Installation
===================

--> Take EC2 instances like (Redhat,, Ubuntu..)

--> Launch the SSH url in GitBash.

--> Update the machine 

	# apt-get update -y

		(or)

	# yum update -y

--> Install Java 

	# apt-get install -y java-1.8.0-openjdk-devel

		(or)

	# yum install -y java-1.8.0-openjdk-devel

--> Install wget

	# apt-get install wget -y

		(or)

	# yum install wget -y 

--> Copy the link "Apache-tomcat version 8 or 9 tar.gz" from apache tomcat website.

	# wget <Copy the link address>

--> Check the list of files 
	
	# ls

--> Un-tar the apache-tomcat 

	# tar -xvf <Paste the .tar file>

--> Change the directory

	# cd <Paste theApache-tomcat blue color file>

--> Check the list of files

	# ls
	
--> Goto bin folder

	# cd bin/

--> Check the list of files

	# ls

--> Start the services 

	# ./start.sh

--> Goto EC2 instance --> Click on Security grps -->All-traffic

--> Copy the PublicIP from the EC2 Instance

--> Goto google paste pubIP:8080

--> Click on manager-App

--> Copy the username link lines

--> Goto apache-tmacte folder

	# cd apache-tomcate/
	
	# cd conf/

	# vi tomcat-user.xml

--> Paste the username link lines in last but one(tomcat users)

-->	 # cd webapps/

	# cd manager/
	
	# cd META-INF/
	
	# vi context.xml (<!--comment the value tag-->,  )

	# cd bin/

	# ./shutdown.sh

	# ./startup.sh

--> Goto google Refresh the apache-tomcat 

--> Enter the username and password

	
	




